cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use the LILA Lab research program, please cite the relevant
  technical report(s) and the LILA-BENI dataset. See individual report
  plans in technical-reports/ for specific citation information.
title: "LILA Lab: Language Intelligence for Low-resource Applications"
authors:
  - family-names: "Nabil"
    given-names: "Ann Naser"
    email: "lila.lab0x@gmail.com"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0006-3561-045X"
    affiliation: "Department of Economics, Jahangirnagar University"
date-released: "2026-06"
version: "1.0"
license: "MIT"
repository-code: "https://github.com/nabil0x/LILA-LAB"
abstract: >-
  LILA Lab (Language Intelligence for Low-resource Applications) is a
  collaborative research platform building NLP measurement infrastructure
  for languages underserved by current AI. This repository contains the
  BENI (Bangla Exploration & Native-language Intelligence) pipeline —
  the flagship XENI pipeline spanning NLP, economics, and computational
  social science — as well as extension frameworks for new languages,
  full communications hub for multi-channel presence, and open research
  collaboration templates.

